		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>In this paper we aim at facilitating generalization for deep networks while supporting interpretability of the learned representations. Towards this goal, we propose a clustering based regularization that encourages parsimonious representations. Our k-means style objective is easy to optimize and flexible, supporting various forms of clustering, such as sample clustering, spatial clustering, as well as co-clustering. We demonstrate the effectiveness of our approach on the tasks of unsupervised learning, classification, fine grained categorization, and zero-shot learning.</p>
			</abstract>
